Launch VS Code.
Open the Command Palette (Ctrl+Shift+P) and type 'shell command' to find the Shell Command: 
    Install 'code' command in PATH command.
Select that option.

To launch Visual Studio Code from inside a Angular project from CLI (Terminal) type:
code .
To launch a terminal window in Visual Studio code type Cntrl+` (This is the backtick key below the esc key)
To add Auto import to VS Code, search for the Auto import plugin and install it.

To generate a new Component from CLI:
ng g c course (Where g stands for generate, c for component and course is the name of the new component)
